1. This is a tragic incident, but it doesn't justify a blanket policy of excluding all asylum seekers and migrants from a country.2. It's important to remember that the vast majority of migrants are law-abiding citizens who contribute positively to their adopted communities.3. Building a wall or restricting immigration based on the actions of a few individuals is not a solution to the complex issue of immigration.4. Instead, we should focus on addressing the root causes of violence and instability in the countries from which these migrants are coming, as well as implementing effective screening and integration programs to ensure the safety and well-being of both the host country and the new arrivals.
